# TEMPLATE — break-glass recovery credential (issue #467). NOT part of the default posture:
# `scripts/gen-secrets.sh` emits it only with `FGENTIC_SECRET_SET=break-glass`, never on the default
# `all` bootstrap or a `rotatable` sweep, so an SSO-only cluster ships no standing recovery admin and
# nothing plaintext in git. The sealed password is the source of truth for a pre-provisioned,
# disabled-by-default local MAS recovery admin used to administer the identity plane when the
# upstream IdP (Keycloak) is unreachable.
#
# "Disabled by default" is layered and enforced outside this Secret: `mas_local_login_enabled` stays
# "false" (clusters/gcp/platform-settings.yaml), and the MAS account is not provisioned or enabled
# until a deliberate, audited GitOps break-glass window. No workload mounts this Secret at rest; an
# operator consumes it through the MAS Admin API / `mas-cli manage` during the window only. Rotation
# is bootstrap-once and live-first (rotate the live MAS account, then re-seal) — see docs/identity.md.
#
# Never commit a real password here. Replace the placeholder only in clusters/<env>/secrets/, where
# `scripts/gen-secrets.sh` writes SOPS ciphertext, and never a decrypted copy.
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
  name: break-glass-recovery
  namespace: matrix
type: kubernetes.io/basic-auth
stringData:
  username: break-glass
  password: REPLACE_WITH_BREAK_GLASS_RECOVERY_PASSWORD
